Field Label:
Earlier, you told me that (insert endorsed symptoms from screener). 


CONTENT OF WORRY


I will first ask you about what you worried about during (that/these times).
Did you worry a lot about things before they happened? (For example, did you worry about starting school in the fall, taking a test, or going to see a doctor?)
Did you worry a lot about little things you've done in the past? (For example, did you worry about how well you behaved or whether you said or did the right thing?)
Did you worry a lot about how well you did your school work?
Did you worry a lot about how good you were in sports or dance or other activities?
Did you worry a lot about whether people liked you?
Did you worry a lot about what other people thought about you?
Did you often ask your parents or teachers if you're doing a good job or doing your work correctly?
When you were uncomfortable with a situation, did you ask a lot of questions of your parents to try to make yourself feel better?
What other kinds of things did you worry about during (that/these times)?
INTERVIEWER: Code content of worries in category below.
Things going on in the world (war, terrorism, crime, floods, tornadoes)

Was it hard for you to stop yourself from worrying about this/these thing(s)? 
INTERVIEWER: Code yes if difficult to stop worrying about at least one of these things.)
Do you think you worried too much or more than you should?
Did your parents or teachers think you worried too much?
When these worries were the worst, how often did you have them?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Less than half the days | 2, About half the days | 3, Most days | 4, Every day | 9, Don't know

Field Label:
SYMPTOMS


I just asked you about different worries that you have.  Now I will ask you if you get any physical feelings in your body when you worry.
When you were worrying about (list things mentioned), did you:
Get headaches or stomachaches, lump in your throat or other physical problems even when you were not sick?
Feel like you had butterflies in your stomach a lot?
Have problems relaxing or feel very tense?
Feel very restless or jumpy, like it was hard to sit still?

Have trouble keeping your mind on things? 
 (Probe: Were you so nervous you couldn't concentrate?)
Find that your mind sometimes went blank?
Feel more grouchy, irritable, or bothered even by little things?
Have tight muscles or feel achy?
Feel tired when you woke up in the morning?
If yes to symptoms, When these problems were the worst, how often did you have them?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Less than half the days | 2, About half the days | 3, Most days | 4, Every day | 9, Don't know
